                                                                                                               Oracle move
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, Sept. 27: California-based IT vendor Oracle seeks to capture the increasing demand for enterprise solutions in the telecom and utilities sectors in India.         
	Telecom and utilities (gas, electric, water and power firms) are the two growing sectors in India where there is a huge demand for complete enterprise solutions, said Krishan Dhawan, managing director of Oracle India Private Limited.         
	Most of the new telecom players, including Sistema-Shyam, Unitech, Videocons Datacom and Aircel, are keen on Oracles complete solutions.         
	In the last two years, Oracle Indias applications business saw an increase in net new customers across many industries.         
	The company is also betting on government departments, with defence being one of the prime areas of focus.        
	There is also a good demand from the police, income tax and visa processing departments in India, said Dhawan.         
	About 100 organisations across the country use Oracle applications.         
	Customers who have recently adopted Oracle technology said it reduced cost and increased productivity.         
	There are more than 500 Indian partners such as Wipro, TCS, Infosys and Redington who drive 80 per cent of our businesses in India, said Dhawan.                                                                                                                                        
